thread.title_full: Sports Legends Museum Closes To Public, Begins Search For New Home

author: Zach Wilt
title: Sports Legends Museum Closes To Public, Begins Search For New Home
text:
Zach Wilt Oct 12, 2015 
Baltimore’s Sports Legends Museum has closed its doors this morning and will begin looking for a new location, according to a tweet from MASNSports.com’s Roch Kubatko. Sports Legends Museum will relocate from Camden Station. Closed to public immediately. Been there since 2005. Search begins for new location 
— Roch Kubatko (@masnRoch) October 12, 2015 
Sports Legends is a non-profit museum operated by the Babe Ruth Birthplace & Museum. It opened on May 14, 2005 and features exhibits on the Baltimore Orioles, Baltimore Ravens, Baltimore Colts, Maryland Terrapins, Baltimore Elite Giants, Baltimore Black Sox, and the Baltimore Blast.
